1. MAC Address (The Physical Identity)

Stands for: Media Access Control.

Simple View: It is the serial number burned into the computer's network card at the factory. It never changes.

Format: Looks like this: 00:1A:2B:3C:4D:5E (Hexadecimal).


2. IP Address (The Logical Location)

Stands for: Internet Protocol.

Simple View: It is the address assigned to your computer based on which network it is currently joined to. It changes if you move to a different Wi-Fi.

Format: Looks like this: 192.168.1.1 (IPv4).

